# Tools – WhyNot Productions

Rules when working on tools. **zerwiz/setup is the main repo.** Develop there, commit there, push there.

## Version control and changelog

- **Main repo for tools:** https://github.com/zerwiz/setup — develop here, commit, PR, changelog, curl delivery
- **Default branch:** `main`. Use feature/fix branches for larger changes (see `rules/services/github/rules.md`).
- **Changelog:** Update `doc/CHANGELOG.md` in zerwiz/setup before every commit that changes behavior or content.
- **Commit messages:** Prefer conventional style: `feat: ...`, `fix: ...`, `docs: ...`, `chore: ...`.
- **Credentials:** Stored locally only, gitignored. Never commit real credentials.

## Deployment

- **Tools live in zerwiz/setup.** Push directly to zerwiz/setup.
- **Curl URLs:** All commands point to raw.githubusercontent.com/zerwiz/setup only.

